HEADWORD: Torana
<hw>To"ra*na</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>
}</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Skr. <ets>t⟦omac⟧ra⟦nsdot⟧a</ets> an arch,
a gate.]</ety> <fld>(Indian Arch.)</fld> <def>A gateway, commonly of
wood, but sometimes of stone, consisting of two upright pillars carrying
one to three transverse lintels. It is often minutely carved with
symbolic sculpture, and serves as a monumental approach to a Buddhist
temple.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Torbernite</ent>⟦br⟧
